quran[6]{c,v,t}:
  7,59,"We did send Noah unto his people, and he said, 'O my people! serve God, ye have no god but Him; verily, I fear for you the torment of the mighty day"
  7,60,"Said the chiefs of his people, 'Verily, we do surely see you in obvious error"
  7,61,"Said he, 'O my people! there is no error in me; but I am an apostle from the Lord of the worlds"
  7,62,"I preach to you the messages of my Lord, and I give you sincere advice; and I know from God what ye know not"
  7,63,"What! do ye wonder that there came to you a reminder from your Lord by a man from amongst yourselves, to warn you, and that ye may fear? but haply ye may receive mercy"
  7,64,"But they called him a liar, and we rescued him and those who were with him in the ark; and we drowned those who said our signs were lies, verily, they were a blind people"